====Usage notes====
* Interjectional usage of '''{{m|fr||allez}}''' has gained significant distance (though perhaps not quite complete independence) from the imperative form of {{m|fr|aller}} in which it originated. One consequence of this development is that, while it retains a certain imperative thrust, the interjection is not necessarily affected by [[T-V distinction]] — that is to say, it may be directed toward someone whom the speaker would address with the familiar pronoun {{m|fr|tu}} or the deferential {{m|fr|vous}}. An especially clear demonstration of this phenomenon (arguably the clearest) can be observed in the phrase {{m|fr||allez vas-y|go on, go}} — which appears to be composed of both second-person imperatives (the plural/deferential and familiar singular) of {{m|fr|[[y aller|(y)]] [[aller]]}}, though the first is actually this now-independent interjection. Similar in form, {{m|fr||allez viens|come on then}} — in which the interjection is joined by the familiar imperative of {{m|fr|venir||to come}}.
* The corresponding familiar imperative {{m|fr|va}} is also used as an interjection, overlapping with '''{{m|fr||allez}}''' in some uses, distinct in others.

